344
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:50,260
I don’t know if I have any left.

345
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,640
[Perfect Foot Mask]

346
00:28:54,580 --> 00:28:58,250
This is it. Centella.

347
00:28:58,250 --> 00:29:01,290
The magical weapon of a date, up you go!

348
00:29:08,090 --> 00:29:10,850
I have to take good care of myself from head to toe.

349
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:14,700
Then my skin will be fair, soft, and smooth.

350
00:29:20,460 --> 00:29:21,850
Not good.

351
00:29:21,850 --> 00:29:23,410
This doesn’t pass.

352
00:29:33,350 --> 00:29:35,750
Moisture level is okay. Gloss is okay.

353
00:29:35,750 --> 00:29:38,730
Women have to be perfect from head to toe.

354
00:29:38,730 --> 00:29:40,420
Perfect.

355
00:30:10,700 --> 00:30:14,160
♫ Lost to you ♫

356
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:23,270
♫ I think of you until I can no longer breathe ♫

357
00:30:23,270 --> 00:30:26,530
♫ My last wish is to never regret ♫

358
00:30:26,530 --> 00:30:32,610
♫ Brave out the heartbreak to no longer be afraid of heartbreaks ♫

359
00:30:32,610 --> 00:30:39,100
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

360
00:30:45,300 --> 00:30:47,030
I passed by

361
00:30:48,370 --> 00:30:50,410
and saved an old, poor guy.

362
00:30:50,410 --> 00:30:52,090
Take it.

363
00:31:06,810 --> 00:31:09,950
It's just a typical modest suite.

364
00:31:13,900 --> 00:31:16,380
So people can actually live in such small places.

365
00:31:18,230 --> 00:31:21,130
This author must have seen Meteor Garden before.

366
00:31:21,130 --> 00:31:24,060
She's even paying tribute to Dao Mingsi's lines.

367
00:31:27,450 --> 00:31:30,570
I'm saying, it's been cleaned really well.

368
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,400
You typically look disorganized,

369
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:40,010
but once you do things, you're pretty meticulous.

370
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,320
Don't worry.

371
00:31:55,970 --> 00:31:58,290
You treat this as a trash can?

372
00:31:59,340 --> 00:32:02,930
Have you ever heard of a physics law?

373
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:05,200
Water flows towards lower elevations.

374
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:07,710
It's just like a trashcan that is lower than the couch.

375
00:32:07,710 --> 00:32:11,880
It slowly falls into the trashcan.

376
00:32:12,810 --> 00:32:15,290
This is a law of nature.

377
00:32:17,370 --> 00:32:19,340
Do you have tea here?

378
00:32:19,340 --> 00:32:21,900
I need some tea to relieve my shock.

379
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:24,160
Wait, don't!

380
00:32:36,930 --> 00:32:39,020
You might have heard of a Buddhist saying.

381
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:41,760
That is everything depends on fate.

382
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:43,470
I have always been waiting for a certain feeling.

383
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:46,950
Once the feeling comes, then I can put them away.

384
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,480
You must at least have drinks.

385
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,580
You don't want to open it.

386
00:32:58,460 --> 00:32:59,990
Okay.

387
00:33:05,230 --> 00:33:07,200
What happened?

388
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:38,930
I don't know why you came.

389
00:33:38,930 --> 00:33:42,430
If you're hurt, why don't you quickly take care of it?

390
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:45,160
I missed you.

391
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:51,460
Overbearing CEOs are just like that,

392
00:33:51,460 --> 00:33:55,250
charming someone in a moment without knowing themselves.

393
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,100
Hey.

394
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:20,720
Do you know who the last woman who did this got in the end?

395
00:34:20,720 --> 00:34:23,110
Prince Chiaki.

396
00:34:24,510 --> 00:34:26,290
You're just an overbearing CEO.

397
00:34:26,290 --> 00:34:28,840
You're even pickier than a prince.

398
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:31,400
Then go with the prince.

399
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,970
I don't want to.

400
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:41,320
I seriously evaluated your home.

401
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:43,510
This environment really isn't good.

402
00:34:43,510 --> 00:34:48,180
Do you want to listen to a business tycoon's sincere suggestion?

403
00:34:48,180 --> 00:34:49,800
What?

404
00:34:51,690 --> 00:34:53,840
Come live with me.

405
00:34:58,740 --> 00:35:00,390
I don't want to.

406
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:02,490
I wanted to say this earlier.

407
00:35:02,490 --> 00:35:05,040
Living in such a big house is tiring.

408
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:08,940
There's no place like home.

409
00:35:13,950 --> 00:35:15,920
Come.

410
00:35:22,970 --> 00:35:24,720
Lie down.

411
00:35:40,850 --> 00:35:42,300
Hey.

412
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:45,550
Don't worry. Those haven't been opened.

413
00:35:46,430 --> 00:35:48,000
Give them to me.

414
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:51,420
Hurry up.

415
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:05,550
This distance was determined through precise calculations.

416
00:36:05,550 --> 00:36:09,700
Snacks can't be farther than an arm's length away.

417
00:36:23,010 --> 00:36:24,970
Tissue.

418
00:36:35,940 --> 00:36:37,460
Don't you want a drink?

419
00:36:37,460 --> 00:36:39,460
Kick the couch.

420
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:41,210
What?

421
00:36:59,420 --> 00:37:00,960
Get up.

422
00:37:06,030 --> 00:37:08,820
Hey, what are you doing?

423
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,720
Relax.

424
00:37:17,720 --> 00:37:19,440
Relax your arms.

425
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:22,240
Relax your body and your face.

426
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:25,990
Relax your expression.

427
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:30,990
Today, you're the most relaxed person in the universe.

428
00:37:30,990 --> 00:37:35,400
Imagine yourself floating on the water.

429
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,770
Wait.

430
00:37:48,520 --> 00:37:50,720
Raise your arm up.

431
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:19,970
If you want, there is also hot tea.

432
00:38:23,250 --> 00:38:25,260
You don't need to get up and boil hot water?

433
00:38:25,260 --> 00:38:27,650
Hot water is over there.

434
00:38:27,650 --> 00:38:29,590
Lift your leg.

435
00:38:30,470 --> 00:38:34,150
45 degrees. Push down.

436
00:38:50,020 --> 00:38:53,010
Wow, how accurate.

437
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:57,090
You see, as long as you aim for the TV's upper right corner,

438
00:38:57,090 --> 00:38:59,250
you won't miss in ten thousand tries.

439
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:12,950
Is there anything else to throw?

440
00:39:20,940 --> 00:39:22,510
It's too light.

441
00:39:22,510 --> 00:39:24,960
Test your skills.

442
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:27,380
Test your skills...

443
00:39:42,070 --> 00:39:43,400
Zheng Xiao'en.

444
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:45,010
What?

445
00:40:12,700 --> 00:40:14,150
[One more bag]

446
00:40:14,150 --> 00:40:16,920
I won! Another bag of chips!

447
00:40:20,110 --> 00:40:22,180
You're really weird.

448
00:40:24,340 --> 00:40:27,980
Weird in a good way or a bad way?

449
00:40:32,610 --> 00:40:35,130
You say you love money,

450
00:40:35,130 --> 00:40:39,190
but you still haven't cashed in the check I gave you.

451
00:40:39,190 --> 00:40:43,470
You never opened the luxury bags and gifts I gave you,

452
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:49,680
but you're so happy because you won a snack.

453
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:55,730
Zheng Xiao'en, the way you love money is so weird.

454
00:40:56,330 --> 00:40:58,430
It's not weird.

455
00:40:59,080 --> 00:41:01,450
It's not weird?

456
00:41:01,450 --> 00:41:04,890
I am really more and more curious about what kind of person you are.

457
00:41:04,890 --> 00:41:08,970
I'm just... an ordinary person.

458
00:41:10,490 --> 00:41:13,070
You're not ordinary at all.

459
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:19,950
How could the woman that I, Situ Aoran, fall for be an ordinary woman?

460
00:41:25,180 --> 00:41:31,970
To me, you're the most special one in the world.

461
00:41:38,770 --> 00:41:40,420
Aoran.

462
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:04,060
Wait for me.

